-startups

Today, David Ellison=E2=80=99s Paramount announced that it will acquire The=
 Free Press [ https://substack.com/redirect/1935d83e-1e5d-44df-9eed-fdb014b=
6c069?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ]=
=E2=80=94founded by Bari Weiss, Suzy Weiss, and Nellie Bowles, and powered =
by Substack=E2=80=94for a reported price of $150 million. While much of the=
 commentary about the deal has focused on the characters involved, we belie=
ve the most remarkable feature of this story is that a media startup went f=
rom zero to a nine-figure outcome in the space of three years, at a time wh=
en many have been led to believe that news is a dying business.
As much as this deal feels like a seismic event in the media business, it w=
on=E2=80=99t be the last of its kind. The media is going through a volatile=
 transition as the industry adjusts to the ongoing ramifications of the int=
ernet and the start of the AI age, but the public=E2=80=99s appetite for tr=
ustworthy storytelling is greater than ever. While some of the giants of ye=
sterday are struggling to survive this transition, there is an immense oppo=
rtunity for ambitious new media founders to build a new generation of insti=
tutions.
The Free Press is one such institution, and it is one among many on Substac=
k, collectively accounting for millions of paid subscribers. Among this new=
 class are Sarah Longwell=E2=80=99s politics collective The Bulwark [ https=
://substack.com/redirect/25a47a2a-3dab-4217-a7e8-de3e1f9fc7e2?j=3DeyJ1IjoiM=
W5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], Mehdi Hasan=E2=80=
=99s Zeteo [ https://substack.com/redirect/fa3f5522-feb2-40f5-a184-6702f7c1=
810b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ],=
 Jeremy Scahill and Ryan Grim=E2=80=99s Drop Site [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/84537e7f-f32d-48ab-a4bc-70d957adf555?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm=
-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], Jen Rubin and Norm Eisen=E2=80=99s =
The Contrarian [ https://substack.com/redirect/e3fea23b-7930-45b1-bf46-fd8f=
be38da01?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3y=
s ], Richard Rushfield and Janice Min=E2=80=99s The Ankler [ https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/067a0292-99a1-49fa-80d5-a56aee01273c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn=
0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], Mike Solana=E2=80=99s Pira=
te Wires [ https://substack.com/redirect/8913ff46-597a-46da-9cfa-fa751d21ce=
88?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], J=
erusalem Demsas=E2=80=99s The Argument [ https://substack.com/redirect/7ed9=
1783-3d32-4189-8fa4-0d61028fe9ff?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZ=
XCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], and JD Flynn and Ed Condon=E2=80=99s Catholic =
news outlet The Pillar [ https://substack.com/redirect/c256b16d-cfef-44c9-b=
452-c1ab0c3f0b4d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecH=
mePkbA3ys ], to name a few.
We=E2=80=99re also seeing the emergence of new models that take advantage o=
f Substack=E2=80=99s network-centric design and flexible features, includin=
g Katelyn Jetelina=E2=80=99s Your Local Epidemiologist [ https://substack.c=
om/redirect/1a4165aa-5adf-43c7-9fe0-8db8f446523e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.Ag=
I-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], which recently sprouted local =
variants in California [ https://substack.com/redirect/d12cbbed-1060-4aef-b=
840-69acaecb16ab?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecH=
mePkbA3ys ] and New York [ https://substack.com/redirect/d3264a8f-509f-4b8c=
-906c-4fbbb6dd9631?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9e=
cHmePkbA3ys ], and spinoff publications created and funded by individual wr=
iters who have found success on the platform, such as Judd Legum (Popular I=
nformation [ https://substack.com/redirect/1717937f-4221-4c73-926d-6a6c1dbd=
bd5b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ] =
and Oligarch Watch [ https://substack.com/redirect/6aba733b-5dea-419f-b401-=
f9af5d1ff2eb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePk=
bA3ys ]) and Matt Yglesias, who started the Slow Boring [ https://substack.=
com/redirect/aee85933-9b61-4ed0-90fe-388b2bc72811?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.A=
gI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ] newsletter as well as Politix =
[ https://substack.com/redirect/682e2965-d171-4ab5-9427-86116f2cf014?j=3Dey=
J1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], a podcast =
co-hosted with Brian Beutler (Yglesias is also a contributor to The Argumen=
t). Emily Sundberg has used her newsletter, Feed Me [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/fe013020-a50f-4752-92b1-5149e78ce736?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-v=
vm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ], as a base for expansion into audi=
o and events, and Lenny Rachitsky has turned his tech expertise into a ramp=
antly successful media business [ https://substack.com/redirect/9a1b9807-7a=
47-4993-8e48-6b8d9225c1f5?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu=
_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ] that encompasses text, audio, video, a community, and =
a premium bundle of AI tools made available to subscribers.
These founders are building here because they can enjoy the distribution be=
nefits of the Substack network=E2=80=94which drives more than 30% of all pa=
id subscriptions across the platform=E2=80=94without compromising their vis=
ion. That network growth and discovery via the app means a media business c=
an now scale faster, and more cost efficiently, than ever before.
What once took months to research, compose, and activate is now available o=
ut of the box. The founders of The Free Press and Zeteo didn=E2=80=99t need=
 to hire developers, wrestle with a dated content management system, or str=
ess about subscriber profile management. They can instead dedicate almost a=
ll of their focus to the work that matters most: their journalism.
In today=E2=80=99s media environment, independent voices who have a direct =
relationship with their audiences are beacons for a better system. As more =
of these publishers succeed on Substack, we provide them with infrastructur=
e that flexes to meet their growing ambitions. This new generation of entre=
preneurs are producing media companies that bear the same commitment to qua=
lity that was once the sole dominion of legacy media, while equipping thems=
elves to thrive in a world of decentralized authority and diminished trust =
in public institutions=E2=80=94including the media itself.
Substack was first a place for creators to start a publication and communit=
y. Now it=E2=80=99s also a place for entrepreneurs to launch entire network=
s. These founders are the future, showing the way forward to a media ecosys=
tem that can be richer, deeper, more open, and more valuable than what has =
come before.
If you are energized by the idea of building the next generation of the med=
ia, then please let us assure you: there has never been a better time to st=
art.
Let=E2=80=99s build the future of media [ https://substack.com/redirect/98e=
72915-0eb5-4b22-a918-6a7e883b0978?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCw=
ZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecHmePkbA3ys ] together.

